1325:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * 				   \b Range: @ref XMC_USIC0_CH0, @ref XMC_USIC0_CH1 to @ref XMC_USIC2_CH1 based on device su
1326:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * @return Status of data validity check for RBUF0 and RBUF1. \n
1327:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * 		   Returned value should be masked with RDV0 and RDV1 bits to know the status. \n
1328:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * 		   \b Range: @ref XMC_USIC_CH_RBUF_STATUS_DATA_VALID0, @ref XMC_USIC_CH_RBUF_STATUS_DATA_VALID
1329:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  *
1330:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * \par<b>Description</b><br>
1331:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * Checks if RBUF0 and RBUF1 have valid unread data. \n\n
1332:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * It checks the bits RDV0 and RDV1 of the RBUFSR register.
1333:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * Returns the value of RBUFSR masked with bitmasks of RDV0 and RDV1.
1334:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * It can be used to decide whether 2bytes has to be read from RBUF or 1 byte.
1335:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * If both bitmasks XMC_USIC_CH_RBUF_STATUS_DATA_VALID0 and XMC_USIC_CH_RBUF_STATUS_DATA_VALID1
1336:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * are set, then 2 bytes can be read from RBUF. If only either of them is set, then only one byte
1337:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * can be read from RBUF.
1338:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_usic.h ****  * \par<b>Related APIs:</b><BR>
